cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically semantic segmentation, which falls under the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also involves graphics hardware and game engines, which could fall under the cs.GR sub-category. The approach presented in the paper involves using machine learning techniques to rapidly generate pixel-accurate semantic label maps, which could fall under the cs.LG sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves using synthetic data to supplement real-world data, which could fall under the cs.AI sub-category. Finally, the paper involves using computer games as a source of data, which could fall under the cs.MM sub-category.
